cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 65 miles WSW of St. Petersburg, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: moving north, then turning north-northeast and northeast across the northern Florida peninsula and emerging off the Georgia coast into the western Atlantic
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: north-central Gulf coast of Florida near or just south of Cedar Key

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical Storm Watch in effect only for north of the Suwannee River to Aucilla River, FL (Big Bend area); no watches along the Georgia coast
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning along Florida west coast from Bonita Beach to Suwannee River; none for Georgia
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Florida west coast, northern Florida peninsula, Georgia coast (including Brunswick), South Carolina coast
weather_observation.wind: Tropical-storm-force gusts (34–45 kt) are possible at Brunswick beginning early Thursday, peaking Thursday afternoon before the center moves offshore.
weather_observation.storm_surge: No significant storm-surge inundation forecast for the Georgia coast from Eta.
weather_observation.rainfall: Bands of rain may bring 1–2 inches; localized totals unlikely to exceed 4 inches.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Dangerous surf and rip currents possible along the Georgia beaches on Thursday.
